UID:395@bwa-calendar
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260326
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260327
SUMMARY:BWA: Easter Bake Sale
DESCRIPTION:Easter Bake Sale to raise funds for the Year 6 school trip to France.\n\nBake sale held from 3pm-4pm. Donations of nut-free baked goods can be dropped off at the main school gate between 8:15am-9:00am on the day. Payments accepted via cash or card.
CATEGORIES:COMMUNITY
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:394@bwa-calendar
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260515
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260516
SUMMARY:BWA: International Families Day
DESCRIPTION:Celebration of diverse and international family community at BWA with national dress, assembly, and after-school buffet.\n\nPupils are invited to wear national dress or flag colours. Homework projects celebrating heritage are due to class teachers by Monday 11th May. An international buffet will be held in the lower hall from 3:30pm. Food donations can be dropped at the school office from 2:30pm. Volunteers to share culture/heritage should sign up by Friday 8th May.
CATEGORIES:COMMUNITY
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:397@bwa-calendar
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260227
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260305
SUMMARY:BWA: Scholastic Book Fair
DESCRIPTION:The school book fair will be open to parents and carers in the middle hall after school.\n\nBelleville Wix Academy will be hosting a Scholastic Book Fair. The fair gives children a fantastic opportunity to enjoy reading and discover new books. Open to parents and carers in the middle hall after school.
CATEGORIES:ARTS
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:399@bwa-calendar
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260420
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260711
SUMMARY:BWA: Summer Term Extra-Curricular Clubs Start
DESCRIPTION:Summer term extra-curricular clubs run for 11 weeks.\n\nSummer term extra-curricular clubs for pupils. All clubs start on the week commencing Monday 20th April and end on Friday 10th July. Note: Monday clubs run for 10 weeks due to Bank Holiday on 1st June.
CATEGORIES:SPORTS
END:VEVENT
